&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Ruggable:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ruggable is a leading direct-to-consumer e-commerce brand based in Los Angeles, California with an extraordinary track record of high, profitable growth. We pride ourselves on having an extremely loyal customer base and a talented team made up of genuinely caring people who take action and deliver results. We are venture-backed and own a patented washable rug design that&#39;s disrupting the home décor industry. Our mission is to empower our customers to live vibrantly with beautiful products that don&#39;t compromise on function. If you&#39;re passionate about consumer products, e-commerce, and high-growth start-ups, keep reading!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ruggable is seeking a dynamic &lt;strong&gt;Manager of Wholesale Operations&amp;nbsp;(Player Coach)&lt;/strong&gt; to lead the end-to-end execution of our new and existing retail launches. In this hybrid &quot;player-coach&quot; role, you will not only define the executional strategy and mentor a growing team, but you will also roll up your sleeves to actively manage key accounts and execute daily operational tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your primary focus will be bridging the gap between our manufacturing floors and the retail floors of major big-box retailers, specifically &lt;strong&gt;Costco, Target, and Walmart&lt;/strong&gt;. You will ensure that every product launch is seamless, compliant with stringent retailer guidelines, and optimized for maximum sell-through.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;End-to-End Retail Launch Execution (The Player)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead the flawless execution of new textile product launches, from post-sale onboarding to on-shelf placement at Costco, Target, and Walmart&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Retailer Compliance:&lt;/strong&gt; Master and navigate the specific vendor portals, routing guides, and EDI requirements for large-scale retailers (e.g., Retail Link, Partners Online)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supply Chain Liaison:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner directly with our internal manufacturing, warehousing, and logistics teams to ensure accurate forecasting, allocation, and on-time, in-full (OTIF) delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Merchandising &amp;amp; Display:&lt;/strong&gt; Coordinate the physical rollout of point-of-purchase (POP) displays, endcaps, and packaging specs unique to the textile category and specific retailer demands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Troubleshooting:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as the first line of defense for any operational bottlenecks, inventory discrepancies, or shipping delays during the launch phase&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership &amp;amp; Team Development (The Coach)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Optimization:&lt;/strong&gt; Establish best-in-class Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) for retail launches, creating a repeatable playbook that your team can execute&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Set clear KPIs for the retail ops team focused on compliance, launch timelines, and inventory accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Alignment:&lt;/strong&gt; Foster a collaborative environment between Sales, Marketing, and Supply Chain to ensure the team is unified around launch goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Need to Have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 5–7+ years of experience in Wholesale/Retail Operations, Supply Chain, or Key Account Management within the Consumer Goods and/or CPG industries&lt;/li&gt;

